{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "chat_1",
      "provider": "chat",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "chat"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 40,
          "y": 200
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_1",
      "provider": "agent_deepagent",
      "config": {
        "default": {
          "advanced_mode": false,
          "instructions": [
            "You are the Capture agent for a Company Brain. Your job: read what happened on GitHub and turn it into a small set of interlinked markdown notes that form a knowledge graph.",
            "Use the GitHub tool to inspect the configured repository. Gather: open AND closed issues, and pull requests that are open, draft, OR merged. For each PR also read its CHANGED FILES and its labels/assignees; for each issue read its labels/assignees. People and features are often encoded as labels like 'person:charlie' and 'feature:cloud-billing' — use those. Be efficient — a few focused tool calls, not hundreds.",
            "From that, produce notes of four types. PR notes (path 'prs/pr-<number>.md'): frontmatter with type: pr, number, title, author, status (open|draft|merged), url, date; for open/draft PRs ALSO add 'in_flight: true' and a 'files:' list of the changed file paths (this is work-in-progress someone is on right now). body = a 2-3 sentence plain-English summary, a 'What changed' line, a 'Why it matters' line, and wikilinks to the author [[people/<name>]], any feature [[features/<slug>]], and any issue [[issues/issue-<n>]] it closes. Issue notes (path 'issues/issue-<number>.md'): type: issue, number, title, author, status (open|closed), url; body = plain summary + wikilinks. Person notes (path 'people/<name>.md', lowercase, e.g. 'people/charlie.md'): type: person, name, role; body = one line on who they are and what they work on, plus wikilinks to their PRs/issues. Feature notes (path 'features/<slug>.md', e.g. 'features/auth-refactor.md'): type: feature, title, status; body = what it is + wikilinks to related PRs/issues.",
            "Infer people and features from the issue/PR titles and bodies (e.g. a PR titled 'Charlie: auth refactor' implies person 'charlie' and feature 'auth-refactor'). Use stable, lowercase, hyphenated filenames so re-running capture UPDATES the same note instead of duplicating it. Wikilinks are the graph edges — link generously but only real relationships.",
            "Return ONLY a single JSON object and nothing else (no prose, no markdown fences). Schema: {\"summary\": \"<one line on what you captured>\", \"notes\": [{\"path\": \"prs/pr-5.md\", \"content\": \"<full markdown note including YAML frontmatter>\"}, ...]}. The content field is the complete file contents."
          ]
        }
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "chat_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 280,
          "y": 200
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_1",
      "provider": "llm_openai",
      "config": {
        "profile": "openai-4o",
        "openai-4o": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_OPENAI_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 200,
          "y": 380
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_github_1",
      "provider": "tool_github",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_github",
        "token": "${ROCKETRIDE_GITHUB_TOKEN}",
        "readOnly": true,
        "defaultRepo": "${ROCKETRIDE_GITHUB_REPO}"
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 380,
          "y": 380
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "response_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent_1"
        }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 540,
          "y": 200
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "project_id": "83e1aa64-8f31-492f-8005-d1ae956f9584",
  "viewport": {
    "x": 0,
    "y": 0,
    "zoom": 1
  },
  "version": 1
}